==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: fertilized
<hw>fertilized</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>united with a male
gamete to begin the development of an individual embryo; -- of female
gametes.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> impregnated, inseminated.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>made more suitable for growth of crops by addition
of fertilizer{2}; -- of soil.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> enriched.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fertilizer</ent>⟦br⟧
